label.value: Stage I Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: IA (T1a, N0, M0); IB (T1b, N0, M0). T1a: Solitary tumor equal to or less than 2 cm.  T1b: Solitary tumor larger than 2 cm without vascular invasion. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Solitary tumor equal to or less than 2 cm.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IB includes: T1b, N0, M0. T1b: Solitary tumor larger than 2 cm without vascular invasion. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0. T2: Solitary tumor larger than 2 cm with vascular invasion, or multiple tumors, none larger than 5 cm. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)
Liquid substances produced by living organisms to fulfill specific functions or excreted as waste. Secretions do not include hormones or enzymes.

label.value: Stage III Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T3, N0, M0); IIIB: (T4, N0, M0). T3: Multiple tumors, at least one of which is larger than 5 cm. T4: Single tumor or multiple tumors of any size involving a major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein, or tumor(s) with direct invasion of adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with perforation of visceral peritoneum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T3, N0, M0. T3: Multiple tumors, at least one of which is larger than 5 cm. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T4, N0, M0. T4: Single tumor or multiple tumors of any size involving a major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein, or tumor(s) with direct invasion of adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with perforation of visceral peritoneum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (Any T, N1, M0); IVB: (Any T, Any N, M1). N1: Regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVA includes: Any T, N1, M0. N1: Regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVB Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVB includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This staging system applies to intrahepatic cholangiocarcinomas, combined hepatocellular-cholangiocarcinomas (mixed hepatocholangiocarcinomas), and primary neuroendocrine tumors of the liver. Primary sarcomas of the liver, pure hepatocellular carcinomas, hilar cholangiocarcinomas, and gallbladder carcinomas are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
